race.comment: Tricky. VERHOEVEN (8) switched from a top Victorian stable and was out of the money resuming over 1200m at Launceston. He was in the market and has the blinkers on for the first time to sharpen him up. He'd be winning this at best and draws better today. The 3kg claim brings him right into it. COAL RIVER (2) returns from a spell having his first run for a new yard. The former Victorian ran his best race placing at Horsham on debut and presents today with some gear changes. Has the inside gate and the ability, and the betting will guide to his readiness. MONCLERE (4) showed good ability early doors and will be better for his two runs back. A 3kg claimer is aboard today and expect improvement. DON TURBOAS (9) ran well on debut placing at Devonport Synthetic. Tricky draw to overcome but fitter deserves consideration.
